main event: The report describes a sighting of two illuminated solid bodies or lights maneuvering in a zigzag manner over Homerville, Ohio on 18th July 1956. The objects vanished over trees after a 3-minute observation.
interesting points: The sighting was categorized as X-S Ground-Radar, Air Visual, and Air Intercept Radar observation.
The witness was a 23-year-old female with no specified special educational training.
The report prompted detailed questions about the sighting, including estimates of speed, distance, and physical characteristics of the objects.
The memo routing slip recommended an explanation for the incident in the report being prepared.
The witness provided handwritten descriptions, including a soft grating noise and the objects appearing white with no quivering or consistency.
sighted object: Two illuminated solid bodies or lights
